title: 44 countries sign Continental Free Trade Area deal in Kigali
description:
Africa's dream of establishing a continental free trade area has moved one step closer to realization after 44 countries signed the agreement in Kigali, Rwanda. About 18 heads of state were present at the signing, including Kenya's Uhuru Kenyatta, South Africa's Cyril Ramaphosa and Ghana's Nana Akufo Addo.
